Syntax: junk <item>

Permanently destroys an item in your inventory, removing it from the game.
Unlike sacrifice, junk gives you nothing in return -- use it only for
items of no value that you simply want to be rid of.

Example:
  junk worn rag     -- Destroys the "worn rag" in your inventory.

The item must be carried (in your inventory), not worn or wielded.

WARNING: Junked items cannot be recovered. Use this command carefully.

See also: sacrifice donate drop
